import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='time')
    plt.plot(data['time'], data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of commits made to Github repositories between January 2015 and May 2015?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['count'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of commits made to Github repositories?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['day'] = data['time'].dt.date
    avg_commits = data.groupby('day')['count'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_commits.index, avg_commits.values, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(avg_commits.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {avg_commits.mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of commits made per day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['day_of_week'] = data['time'].dt.day_name()
    chart_data = data.groupby('day_of_week')['count'].apply(list).reset_index(name='counts')
    chart_data['day_of_week'] = pd.Categorical(chart_data['day_of_week'], categories=['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday'], ordered=True)
    chart_data = chart_data.sort_values('day_of_week')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(chart_data['counts'], vert=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Number of Commits')
    ax.set_ylabel('Day of the Week')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between the day of the week and the number of commits made?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
